comments.body:
@escowles @kelynch I updated the indexing process to attach to the Books' Solr documents the name information found in the Version data. This makes sure the searches work as expected. This required using Solr's [atomic update](https://solr.apache.org/guide/8_9/updating-parts-of-documents.html#atomic-updates) on the Book records but luckily our Solr and RSolr support it.

The total indexing time went up about 2-3 minutes with the new code. Keep in mind that the entire process takes 2+ hours end to end (most of the time is spent fetching manifest data from a bunch of institutions.)
Reopening this until it's been run.
I look forward to finding out!!

figgy.title: Cookie overflow error during index "read-only" context.

comments.body: Flash messages live only until the next request is made. In figgy, it looks like multiple controller actions are called for a single request. For example, when submitting a blank search, the CatalogController hits the `before_action`, but then the Riiif::ImagesController hits the `before_action` multiple times.
We should move the relevant before_actions to just be in the catalog controller. This will ensure the downtime messages show on the home page, search results pages, and show pages.

pulfalight.title: dash vs dot in older figgy records not showing online content

comments.body:
So the ID in Pulfalight was changed in the URL, but the actual call numbers still have periods in them. 

For example: https://aspace.princeton.edu/staff/resources/2161#tree::archival_object_733628 The call number for this is AC107.07_c897. If you put that in Figgy it works fine.

In fact, if you use the "-" version (which is only in the pulfalight URL) in Figgy then I think DAO updating wouldn't work, since it'd try to find the archival object and not find it (there's no "AC107-07_c897"). 

So I think there's a few things to do here:

- [x] Update all instances of "-" in Figgy with "." (this should only be new records I think?)
- [x] Update the Pulfalight javascript that looks up the viewer to use periods instead of dashes.
Records are fixed, ADR is in, and viewer queries appropriately.
